explanations.reason: The paper focuses on assessing health-related quality of life (HRQOL) among adolescents and young adults with and without cancer using propensity score matching and statistical methods like chi-square tests and multiple logistic regression. There is no mention or use of machine learning techniques, neural networks, or any other advanced computational methods listed in the keywords. The study is purely based on traditional statistical analysis and does not involve any of the specified machine learning or deep learning approaches.
